# Remember Context Prompt
I am building a full-stack digital museum / paintings gallery web app.

Frontend
React + TypeScript (Vite)
Chakra UI
Framer Motion
React Router
Current frontend features
Landing page with animations and carousel
Gallery page with:
responsive masonry-style grid
hover interactions
filter UI (tags-based)
search bar (frontend only for now)
Painting Details page (dynamic route /painting/:id)
Navbar + navigation
Backend
Node.js + Express
MongoDB Atlas (Mongoose)
REST API:
GET /api/paintings → all paintings
GET /api/paintings/:id → single painting
Seed script already created and working
Images are served statically from backend using:
/paintings route
images stored in sibling frontend folder:
paintings-project/public/paintings
Data model (Painting)
title
artist
year
medium
description (museum-style text)
imageUrls (array of local server URLs)
tags
relatedPaintings (currently empty, future feature)
Current status
Backend + MongoDB Atlas fully working
Seed data inserted successfully
Images now correctly loading from Express static server
Frontend Gallery already fetching from API instead of mock data
Painting details page is partially implemented but still needs full backend integration improvements
Next goals
Improve Painting Details page (fully dynamic, clean UI)
Implement related paintings properly (based on tags or IDs)
Improve search/filter to use backend later
Prepare architecture for scaling (real museum-like system)
Important context

We are NOT using mock data anymore. Everything is now API-driven.

